          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Doolittle Stitchery is a celebration of artistry, heritage, and the quiet beauty of making something by hand. Founded by artist Elizabeth “Beth” Nagle and her daughters, Tess and Grace, the studio creates needlepoint canvases that feel both timeless and distinctly personal.</strong></p><p><strong>The name traces back to Doolittle Lake in Connecticut, where long summer afternoons were spent stitching side by side—moments of calm, creativity, and connection that continue to shape the spirit of the brand.</strong></p><p><strong>Beth’s lifelong devotion to needlepoint, from her early training in London to decades of design work, lends each canvas a sense of depth and refinement. Her aesthetic is classic yet inviting—rooted in tradition, but never bound by it.</strong></p><p><strong>Together, Tess and Grace bring a new dimension to the studio. Through Hello Tess Designs, Tess introduces a fresh, expressive perspective, while Grace’s work reflects a deep belief in the restorative, almost meditative rhythm of stitching.</strong></p>",
            "text_font_size": "body-large",
            "padding_bottom": 16
          }
        }
